### Iris Flower Classification 
**A complete Machine Learning project to classify Iris species using multiple algorithms**

[Iris Dataset](https://github.com/mahimajai/irisflower_project/assets/123456789/iris-banner.png)  
*Setosa • Versicolor • Virginica – 100% accuracy achieved*

 A model that can classify Iris flowers into three species (Setosa, Versicolor, Virginica) based on sepal and petal measurements.  
**Dataset:** Classic Iris dataset (150 samples, 4 features, 3 balanced classes)  
**Result:** Multiple models trained – **Logistic Regression hits 100% accuracy!**

This project covers the full ML pipeline:
- Data loading & exploration  
- Visualization (pair plots, correlation heatmap)  
- Model training & comparison  
- Evaluation with accuracy, classification report, confusion matrix  

Perfect beginner project that actually works perfectly!

---

### Key Results (Tested on Nov 10, 2025)
| Model                | Accuracy | Notes                          |
|----------------------|----------|--------------------------------|
| Logistic Regression  | **100%** | Perfect separation!            |
| Decision Tree        | 97.37%   | Slightly overfits              |
| K-Nearest Neighbors  | 97.37%   | Great with k=3                 |
| Support Vector Machine | 97.37% | Linear kernel works best      |

**Classification Report (Logistic Regression):**
```
              precision    recall  f1-score   support

      Setosa       1.00      1.00      1.00        11
  Versicolor       1.00      1.00      1.00        13
   Virginica       1.00      1.00      1.00         8

    accuracy                           1.00        32
```



### How It Works (Step-by-Step)
1. Load Iris dataset from sklearn  
2. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)  
   - Pairplot with species coloring  
   - Correlation heatmap  
   - Box plots for feature distribution  
3. Split data (70% train, 30% test)  
4. Train 4 different classifiers  
5. Evaluate and compare  
6. Save the best model (Logistic Regression)  



### Requirements
```bash
pip install scikit-learn pandas seaborn matplotlib numpy
```


### How to Run (Easiest Way – 30 Seconds)
```bash
git clone https://github.com/mahimajai/irisflower_project.git
cd irisflower_project
```

Open in **Google Colab** (zero setup):  
[![Open in Colab](https://colab.research.google.com/assets/colab-badge.svg)](https://colab.research.google.com/github/mahimajai/irisflower_project/blob/main/IRIS_FLOWER.ipynb)

Just click **Run All** → You'll see:
- Beautiful EDA plots  
- Model comparison table  
- Confusion matrix heatmaps  
- 100% accuracy  

